question: Question: Cauchy's tensor represents this quantity and can be broken into hydrostatic and deviatoric pieces, and Young's modulus is the ratio of this quantity to strain.   [10] Name this quantity that is the amount of internal deforming force over the area it acts. The shear type acts parallel to the surface area of the body being deformed.
